Category: Do any of your findings surprise you?
Project Management Specialists: I found it surprising how high the median pay for a Data Scientist is with its growth rate of 34%. Additionally, I found it interesting how out of all the jobs, Management Analyst is the only one that emphasizes years of prior work experience to obtain the title.

Category: Rank the jobs you picked from best to worst, and briefly explain why you did so.
Project Management Specialists: 1. Data Scientist - great pay and growth rate
2. Project Manager - very broad and across multiple industries while aligning well with teachings of my St
3. Industrial Engineer - moderate growth but lower salary
4. Software Developer - great pay but comes with high-stress times
5. Computer Systems Analysis - more tech heavy field that I don't necessarily envision myself in
6. Actuary - has exam requirements spanning over 6 years
7. Mangement Analyst - difficult to get without prior work experience
